parts.text: "I was in a violent domestic abuse assault over the weekend.  My fianc√© of 6 years who I've known for 17 years got very intoxicated and violent and strangled and suffocated me.  I was lucky to get away but I cannot deal."
"I don't feel safe"
"My mom said I can't have any food until I behave."
"He doesn't allow me to talk to anyone else"
"I don't like where I am at"
"I'm scared to say no when they ask me to do bad things"
"They make me do bad things"
"I'm scared to go home"
"I'm afraid"
"She's forcing me to do things."
"She told me I have to do things for her even though I don't want to."
"She won't let me eat"
"They are preventing me from eating."
"I'm not allowed to have any friends"
"Please help me"
"How can they get away with this"
"They make me keep secrets"
"They won't take me to the doctor"
"They're always yelling"
"I'm not allowed to talk about what happens at home"
"When nobody's looking, my mom abuses me."
